		<div class="question-answer">
			<h2 class="question" id="question">The other team is serving but you can’t see the guy who is serving as the other team players are blocking your view by moving their hand in the net . What should you do? </h2>
			
			<h2 id="explanation">If the other team blockers are just moving their hands,  that’s completely allowed ( even if it is not frowned upon ) . The best thing to do is just to move a couple of steps , as is not allowed to change position. Lastly, telling them to stop wouldn’t do anything .</h2>
		</div>
		
		<div class="answers">
			<div class="answer1" id="answer1">
			
				
				<h3 class = "answer1-text">Let the referee now as that’s not allowed in volleyball</h3>
			</div>
			
			<div class="answer2" id="answer2">
			
				
				<h3 class = "answer2-text">Tell the other team players to stop doing it.</h3>
			</div>
			
			
			<div class="answer3" id="answer3">
				
				
				<h3 class = "answer3-text">Move your position some steps so you can again see the person serving </h3>
			</div>
			
			<div class="answer4" id="answer4">
			
				
				<h3 class = "answer4-text">Change your position with one of your teammates as that way they won’t be able to block your view anymore</h3>
			</div>
		</div>
		
